gomodel:SYNGO_2894  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors show that RNAi induced knockdown of Scribble results in decreased uptake of FM 4-64 at Syn-GFP positive puncta after high potassium stimulation (complete unloading of FM4-64 was observed after restimulation).. Experimental description: Hippocampi from embryonic day 18 (E18) rat, E18 mouse, or postnatal day 1 (P1) B6.129-Ctnnb1tm2Kem/KnwJ mouse (JAX Mice and Services, Bar Harbor, ME) were prepared as previously described (Xie et al., 2000) and plated at a density of 130, 170, and 260 cells/mm2, respectively." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2894" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

